.<img width="1500" height="1000" class="wp-image-1800436" style="width: 800px;" src="https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/Buhari-2.jpg" alt="Buhari confirms Abdulaziz as TCN MD" srcset="https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/Buhari-2.jpg?width=1500&amp;auto_optimize=medium 1500w, https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/Buhari-2-300x200.jpg?width=300&amp;auto_optimize=medium 300w, https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/Buhari-2-1024x683.jpg?width=1024&amp;auto_optimize=medium 1024w, https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/Buhari-2-768x512.jpg?width=768&amp;auto_optimize=medium 768w, https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/Buhari-2-1200x800.jpg?width=1200&amp;auto_optimize=medium 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 1500px) 100vw, 1500px" /> By Johnbosco Agbakwuru, ABUJA PRESIDENT Muhammadu Buhari is currently meeting with the All Progressives Congress, APC, from the north at the Presidential Villa, Abuja. The meeting is coming a day before the commencement of the partyâ€™s convention to elect its presidential candidate for the 2023 general elections. Although President Buhari has maintained his position on the consensus arrangement, there has not been any agreement among the 23 presidential aspirants. The meeting with the APC governors from the north is the fourth parley in his effort to ensure that the party presents a consensus candidate so as to reduce acrimony that may arise at the end of the convention. The governors in attendance are Chairman of Progressive Governors Forum and governor of Kebbi state, Atiku Bagudu, chairman of Northern governors Forum and governor of Plateau State, Simeon Lalong, Abubakar Baduru (Jigawa) and Babagana Zulum (Borno). Others are Aminu Bello Masari (Katsina), Abdullahi Sule (Nasarawa), Bello Matawale (Zamfara), Mallam Nasir el-Rufai (Kaduna), Abdullahi Ganduje (Kano), Yahaya Inuwa (Gombe), Abubakar Bello (Niger), and the Yobe State governor, Mai Mala Buni. As at the time of sending this report, only the governor of Kogi, Yahaya Bello was yet to arrive.